 within the city, he was forced to walk a razor's edge to keep himself, and those he cared about safe.%0a%3c %0a%3c Within two years of coming to town, the Speakeasy was up and running, and Remy was creating a reputation for himself.  Some knew him as the 'Baron', for he walked that fine like between life and death, working with each faction, carefully, only showing force when absolutely needed, and making sure that each show of force was a lesson to at least one of the factions when it was done.  He rarely had an issue with the Wise or the Lost, but the Kindred and the Uratha seemed to take special interest in Remy and his dealings.%0a%3c %0a%3c '+Downtime at the Speakeasy+'%0a%3c %0a%3c The Speakeasy is truly the one crowning achievement of Remy's, and it's seen it's fair share of use throughout the years.  From the smuggler tunnels that lead around parts of the city to allow access with secret panels, to the shop above it, Remy's taken his time to care for it properly, to the point one would imagine that it was his first love.  Parties, events, meetings, debates, negotiations...  All manner of things occur here, and Remy loves the fact that he can help it happen there.  In ages long gone, the Rose City Guild met there on occasion, a place to discuss things where there were rules, but not laws.  It continues on to this day, with Remy watching over the place and the proceedings with the keen eye of a man who loves the place with all his heart.%0a---%0a> !! Hooks%0a> %0a> * Big Game Hunting - chances are, if you're looking to hunt anything supernatural, Eric will gladly join you. If only the word "hunt" was less open to interpretation...%0a> * Make New Friends, But Keep the Old - Eric is growing increasingly adept at contacting the deceased. If you're missing a loved one who died, or if you're just after a secret someone took to their grave, ask Eric what you can do about that...%0a> * Always Be Learning - Eric knows people who know people in Academia. His connectio